parts.text: A formal Freedom of Information request was lodged and granted for the 2023 Referendum Writ. While the document indicates "Release in full" with "N/A" for exemptions, suggesting transparency, it simultaneously highlights potential bureaucratic inefficiency. The writ is explicitly noted as "available at aec.gov.au," raising questions about why a formal FOI process was necessary to access a document that should be proactively and readily available without administrative hurdles. This points to a system where citizens may be forced into formal requests for basic public information, rather than a genuine commitment to effortless public access and proactive disclosure. The "transparency" demonstrated is merely the bare minimum fulfillment of a request for a fundamentally public document, rather than an indicator of robust, proactive openness regarding government operations.
